    </ol>
  </nav>

  <!-- Section 1 -->
  <section>
    <h2 id="purpose">1. Purpose of This Policy</h2>
    <p>1.1 To set out clear procedures for the admission of staff, pupils, parents, contractors and visitors to the School site, aligned with the School's Safeguarding Policy and fire evacuation procedures.</p>
    <p>1.2 To safeguard all pupils so they can learn in a safe, secure and well-managed environment.</p>
    <p>1.3 To ensure that staff, pupils, parents and visitors feel safe and confident while on campus.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2 -->
  <section>
    <h2 id="scope">2. Scope</h2>
    <p>2.1 The School has responsibility for pupils during the school day and during any school-organised activities outside normal hours.</p>
    <p>2.2 This policy applies to the whole School community, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>All teaching and non-teaching staff</li>
      <li>All pupils</li>
      <li>All parents and parent volunteers</li>
      <li>All external visitors</li>
      <li>All vehicles entering the School site</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3 -->
  <section>
    <h2 id="procedures">3. Procedures</h2>

    <h3 id="school-staff">3.1 School Staff</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>All staff must display their School ID card and wear the approved staff lanyard at all times while on campus.</li>
      <li>Staff must not enter restricted or unauthorised areas unless access is required for their role and has been approved.</li>
      <li>Staff are responsible for ensuring that visitors under their supervision follow School procedures.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="pupils">3.2 Pupils</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>All pupils must enter and leave the School in School uniform unless permission has been granted otherwise.</li>
      <li>Pupils arriving late must report to the designated School entrance and sign in before going to class.</li>
      <li>Pupils must carry their pupil ID card at all times.</li>
      <li>Pupils leaving early must obtain written approval from the School Office and present this to security before leaving, even when collected by a parent.</li>
      <li>Pupils may not leave campus during the school day unless authorised by the School.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="visitors-with-appointments">3.3 Visitors with Appointments</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Staff expecting visitors must inform Reception in advance, providing the visitor's name, purpose, date and time of visit.</li>
      <li>All visitors must enter through Security at the main gate before entering the campus.</li>
      <li>Visitors must sign in, state the purpose of their visit, and identify the staff member they are visiting.</li>
      <li>Visitors must present official photo identification.</li>
      <li>Visitors must wear the School-issued visitor pass at all times.</li>
      <li>Visitors must be collected from Reception by their host and remain accompanied at all times unless prior safeguarding clearance has been approved.</li>
      <li>On departure, visitors must sign out and return their visitor pass at the gate.</li>
      <li>Visitor parking must be pre-arranged and is subject to availability. Security instructions must be followed at all times.</li>
      <li>Only visitors who have completed appropriate safeguarding and background checks, approved by the School's Designated Safeguarding Lead, may be granted limited unaccompanied access for School business.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="visitors-without-appointments">3.4 Visitors without Appointments</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Visitors without an appointment must report to Reception to determine whether a meeting can be arranged.</li>
      <li>If no staff member is available, access will not be granted and an alternative appointment should be arranged.</li>
      <li>Any individual on site without a visible staff or visitor pass must be politely challenged and escorted to Reception.</li>
      <li>Visitors who refuse to comply will be asked to leave immediately. Senior Leadership will be informed and police may be contacted if required.</li>
      <li>Any aggressive or abusive behaviour will result in immediate removal from the site.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="contractors">3.5 Contractors and External Service Providers</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>All contractors and service providers must register at Reception, present identification and wear the correct contractor or service lanyard.</li>
      <li>Contractors must follow all School safety and safeguarding procedures.</li>
      <li>Contractors must remain accompanied by a member of School staff unless prior approval has been given.</li>
      <li>Contractors without valid identification or authorisation will be removed from site immediately.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4 -->
  <section>
    <h2 id="drop-off-pick-up">4. Drop-Off and Pick-Up Arrangements</h2>

    <h3 id="general-principles">4.1 General Principles</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>These procedures are in place to ensure pupil safety and smooth traffic flow.</li>
      <li>All instructions given by security staff must be followed.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="pedestrian-access">4.2 Pedestrian Access</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>All pedestrian drop-off and collection must take place via the designated School gates.</li>
      <li>Pedestrians must use marked walkways and follow security directions.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="vehicles">4.3 Vehicles</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>The maximum speed limit on campus is 8 km/h.</li>
      <li>Vehicles may only stop in designated drop-off and pick-up zones.</li>
      <li>Drivers must not leave vehicles unattended.</li>
      <li>Vehicles must exit the campus promptly after drop-off or collection.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="drop-off">4.4 Drop-Off</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Pupils should be ready to exit vehicles promptly.</li>
      <li>Parents or drivers should remain in vehicles at all times.</li>
      <li>Waiting time in drop-off zones is strictly limited.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="pick-up">4.5 Pick-Up</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Gates will open only at published pick-up times.</li>
      <li>Vehicles arriving early will be asked to queue off-site if necessary.</li>
      <li>Vehicles may be asked to re-queue if pupils are not ready at the collection point.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="penalties">4.6 Penalties</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Failure to comply with traffic or security instructions may result in a warning.</li>
      <li>Repeated breaches may result in withdrawal of vehicle access privileges.</li>
      <li>Abuse towards security or staff will result in immediate action by the School.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5 -->
  <section>
    <h2 id="deliveries">5. Deliveries</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>All deliveries must be arranged through school administration and directed to the designated delivery area.</li>
      <li>Staff should not arrange personal deliveries to the School unless specifically authorised.</li>
      <li>Security reserves the right to refuse unauthorised deliveries.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 6 -->
  <section>
    <h2 id="compliance">6. Compliance</h2>
    <p>Failure to follow this policy may result in restricted access to the campus and further action in line with School procedures.</p>
  </section>

</PolicyLayout>
